I just watched the movie and I think Snow White was FANTASTIC! The music was incredible, the scenes were beautiful, but what I really enjoyed the most was the simple, pure, good-vs-evil plot where good wins and evil loses. Snow White is a story of how Christ-like leadership--principles of selflessness, virtue, generosity, kindness, compassion, and grace--leads people to prosperity and true happiness. It contrasts this against the darkness of greed and jealously and clearly yet wonderfully teaches that these evil tendencies lead to sadness and spiritual poverty in individuals and nations. In the end, good wins, and evil is consumed by it's own pride. The leader who cares about others and knows their names is chosen by the people. The leader who seeks only for her own interests is destroyed by her greed. This is the type of story I can raise my children on. This is the type of story that makes society better.

Congratulations. Really. Bravo to everyone who boycotted Snow White hoping it would fail. You succeeded : the film didn‚Äôt do well at the box office. Mission accomplished. But here‚Äôs the flip side : Thanks to this failure, many projects that people were genuinely excited about have now been canceled. Aladdin 2 ‚Äî scrapped. Hercules ‚Äî suspended during the script phase. Rapunzel ‚Äî the long-awaited project ? Cancelled. So yes, you got what you wanted. But at what cost ? The irony is that Snow White still found significant success in home media sales. The film is now ranked among the top-selling physical releases worldwide. And those who bought it ? They keep it for life. Unlike a cinema ticket, a DVD doesn‚Äôt fade away. So in the end, you made a lot of noise‚Ä¶ but for what ? The result : cancelled films, an actress targeted, entire teams demoralized‚Ä¶ And a movie that still managed to reach an audience‚Äîsimply because some people chose to give it a chance. Once again, well done. Truly. üëè
